We need a way to decode a single PartyResult. We can&#39;t use Decodable directly here, because we need to pass in the name, but that&#39;s ok. We can make our own `init` that accepts a container and a name. I&#39;m assuming you want a default of 0 for values that are missing (rather than making them optional).

    struct PartyResult {
        enum CodingKeys: String, CodingKey {
            case dagegenGestimmt = &quot;dagegen gestimmt&quot;
            case nichtBeteiligt = &quot;nicht beteiligt&quot;
            case daf&#252;rGestimmt = &quot;daf&#252;r gestimmt&quot;
